    "title": "Developing a Swift package in tandem with an app"
  },
  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Swift packages are a convenient and lightweight solution for creating a modular app",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "architecture and reusing code across your apps or with other developers. Over time,",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "you may want to develop your published Swift package in tandem with your app, or",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "create a sample app to showcase its features. To develop a Swift package in tandem",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "with an app, you can leverage the behavior whereby a local package overrides a package",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": " ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "text": "dependency with the same name:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Add the Swift package to your app as a package dependency instead of a local package,",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "as described in ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "identifier": "doc://com.apple.Xcode/documentation/Xcode/editing-a-package-dependency-as-a-local-package",
                      "isActive": true,
                      "type": "reference"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": ".",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "Develop your app and your Swift package in tandem, and push changes to their repositories.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "inlineContent": [
                    {
                      "text": "If you release a new version of your Swift package or want to stop using the local",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": " ",
                      "type": "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text": "package, remove it from the project to use the package dependency again.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type": "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type": "orderedList"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
